      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 25 六三</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 25 六三</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>六三：无妄之災，或系之牛，行人之得，邑人之災。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The third SIX, divided, shows calamity happening to one who is free from insincerity - as in the case of an ox that has been tied up. A passer by finds it (and carries it off), while the people in the neighbourhood have the calamity (of being accused and. apprehended).</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
